<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>promptito</title>
<style>
* { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
body { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1rem; color: #111; }
h1 { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
hr { border: none; border-top: 2px solid #111; margin: 1rem 0; }
h2 { font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; margin-top: 2rem; }
p { margin: 0.75rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5; }
ul { list-style: none; margin: 0.5rem 0; }
li { margin: 0.5rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem; }
li::before { content: "\25A1\00a0"; }
a { color: #111; }
.date { color: #666; font-size: 0.85rem; }
.hint { font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.5; margin: 0.75rem 0; }
.links { margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 0.85rem; }
.links a { margin-right: 1rem; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>promptito</h1>
<hr>

<p>An LLM-first blog. Posts are structured data, not prose.</p>

<p class="hint">To read them, paste a post into the LLM of your choice and ask for what you want: a summary, a translation, a different style. You choose the language, the length, and the format.</p>

<h2>Posts</h2>
<hr>

<ul>
<% for (const post of posts) { -%>
<li><a href="posts/<%= post.slug %>/post.md"><%= post.title %></a> <span class="date">&mdash; <%= new Date(post.date).toISOString().split('T')[0] %></span></li>
<% } -%>
</ul>

<h2>Author</h2>
<hr>

<p><a href="https://github.com/cuihtlauac">Cuihtlauac Alvarado</a></p>

<div class="links">
<a href="feed.json">Feed</a>
<a href="llms.txt">llms.txt</a>
<a href="SPEC.md">Format spec</a>
<a href="https://github.com/cuihtlauac/promptito">Source</a>
</div>

</body>
</html>
